  "prompt": "Is a graduate's starting package a way to measure his talent?",
  "response": "Not necessarily. A graduate's starting package can be influenced by various factors:\n\nPros of using starting package as a talent indicator:\n1. May reflect industry demand\n2. Could indicate skill level\n3. Might suggest potential\n\nCons of using starting package as a sole talent measure:\n1. Depends on industry and location\n2. Can be affected by networking\n3. Influenced by economic conditions\n4. Does not always correlate with actual skills\n5. Might not reflect long-term potential\n6. Can vary based on college reputation\n\nBetter ways to measure talent:\n1. Actual skills and competencies\n2. Problem-solving abilities\n3. Learning potential\n4. Work ethic\n5. Professional achievements\n6. Portfolio/project quality\n\nA starting package is just one data point and should not be considered a comprehensive measure of a graduate's talent or potential.",
